**YES, we collect:**
- Name (from Google Sign-In)
- Email address
- User IDs
- Purchase history (optional product prices)
- App interactions
- In-app search history
- User-generated content (inventory, lists)
- Other actions (usage/wastage tracking)
- Crash logs
- Diagnostics
- Performance data
- Device IDs

**YES, we share with third parties:**
- App interactions ‚Üí Firebase & AdMob
- Crash logs ‚Üí Firebase
- Diagnostics ‚Üí Firebase
- Performance data ‚Üí Firebase
- Device IDs ‚Üí Firebase & AdMob

**Data collection purposes:**
- ‚úÖ App functionality
- ‚úÖ Analytics
- ‚úÖ Advertising or marketing (AdMob)
- ‚úÖ Account management
- ‚úÖ Fraud prevention, security, and compliance

**Security:**
- ‚úÖ Encrypted in transit
- ‚úÖ Users can request deletion
- ‚úÖ Privacy policy provided

---

## Need Help?

If Google Play Console rejects your Data Safety section, common reasons are:
1. Privacy policy doesn't match Data Safety declarations
2. Missing third-party data sharing declarations (Firebase, AdMob)
3. Advertising data collection not properly declared
4. Push notification data not declared

Make sure everything in this guide matches your actual implementation!

